comment: Hill (IND) legally contests Ariza's (HOU) jump shot attempt and allows him to land prior to any incidental body contact.
Mahinmi (IND) makes incidental contact with Beasley (HOU) that does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Mahinmi (IND) sets the screen on Harden (HOU) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
RHH shows that Ariza (HOU) makes contact with Ellis (IND) that affects his RSBQ and causes him to lose control of the ball.
Mahinmi (IND) continues moving as he sets the screen on Ariza (HOU) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Harden (HOU) is already in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds when he moves to toward Hill (IND).
Brewer (HOU) legally contests Ellis' (IND) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
McDaniels' (HOU) left arm makes contact with Mahinmi's (IND) waist and affects his RSBQ.
Howard (HOU) grabs and holds George (IND), affecting his ability to defend.
LATR shows that George (IND) makes incidental contact with Harden (HOU) as they both attempt to obtain the inbound pass. Harden dribbles the ball off George's leg.
Ariza (HOU) commits a take foul on Ellis (IND).
George (IND) and Harden (HOU) engage with one another and do not separate during the inbounds play.
Hill (IND) cleanly strips the ball from Terry (HOU).
[Detectable with stop watch] Beasley (HOU) does not inbound the ball within 5 seconds.
Howard (HOU) makes contact with Ellis (IND) affecting his ability to retrieve the loose ball.
[Incidental or immaterial] PXP and RATR show that Harden (HOU) pushes George (IND) in the chest to create space and affects his ability to defend.
Hill (IND) legally contests Terry's (HOU) jump shot attempt.
